From c90cc3f97d411b4ae1d657fc25eca1aedafaa80b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tony Garnock-Jones <tonyg@leastfixedpoint.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Mar 2026 10:02:47 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 01/15] Implement `SSH_ENABLE_CERT_AUTH` feature for
 user-supplied SSH CA keys.

A new `app.ini` variable, `SSH_ENABLE_CERT_AUTH`, allows Forgejo to accept authorized_keys
lines including options `cert-authority` and/or `principals="..."` in its SSH key management
facility. SSH connections presenting valid certificates signed by such keys ("CA keys") are
then accepted. Each CA key effectively has its own arbitrary namespace of principal names: the
user has freedom to choose any naming system that makes sense. If `principals="..."` is present
for a CA key, then presented certificates must include one of the given names; if it is
omitted, presented certificates default to requiring a principal name equal to the Forgejo
username owning the CA key.
